### Module E: Data Quality Validation

**Problem:** No validation that LLM-extracted prices are reasonable.  
**Solution:** Post-extraction validation layer with configurable rules.

#### [NEW] [data-quality.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/data-quality.ts)

```typescript
interface QualityRule {
  category: string;
  metric: string;        // regex or exact match
  minValue: number;
  maxValue: number;
  unit: string;
}

// Example rules:
// Marble tiles: 50-2000 AED/sqm
// Fitout luxury: 500-5000 AED/sqft
// Kitchen fittings: 500-500000 AED/set

function validateEvidence(record: NormalizedEvidenceInput): QualityResult
function flagOutlier(record, reason): void
```

- Configurable per-category price ranges based on `benchmarkData` table
- Auto-flag outliers (don't reject — flag for review)
- Add `qualityStatus` field tracking: [valid](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/intake/ai-intake-engine.ts#500-510), `outlier_flagged`, `rejected`

#### [MODIFY] [orchestrator.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/orchestrator.ts)

- Call `validateEvidence()` after normalization, before upsert
- Records with `outlier_flagged` still get inserted but with a flag

---

### Module D: Freshness-Triggered Re-scrape

**Problem:** Sources only re-scrape on cron schedule, not when data goes stale.  
**Solution:** Check freshness after each run, auto-queue stale sources for immediate re-scrape.

#### [MODIFY] [scheduler.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/scheduler.ts)

Add `checkAndTriggerStaleRefresh()`:
- After each cron run completes, query `evidence_records` for items where `captureDate` > 90 days
- Group by `sourceRegistryId`
- For any source with >50% stale records, auto-queue a re-scrape
- Cap at 3 auto-triggered re-scrapes per day to avoid API abuse

#### [MODIFY] [freshness.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/freshness.ts)

Add `getStaleSourceIds()` — returns sourceRegistryIds that need re-scraping based on evidence freshness distribution.

