## Phase 3 — Self-Evolving Intelligence (Modules B, H)

### Module B: Source Discovery Engine

**Problem:** New UAE suppliers, developer launches, research reports appear constantly – no automated discovery.  
**Solution:** AI + Firecrawl search to discover, evaluate, and auto-register new sources.

#### [NEW] [source-discovery.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/source-discovery.ts)

```typescript
interface DiscoveredSource {
  url: string;
  name: string;
  sourceType: string;
  grade: "A" | "B" | "C";
  reason: string;
  testScrapeResult?: { recordCount: number; sampleItems: string[] };
}

async function discoverNewSources(
  category: "material_pricing" | "market_trends" | "developer_projects" | "design_inspiration"
): Promise<DiscoveredSource[]>
```

**Flow:**
1. Build search queries per category:
   - Pricing: `"UAE marble supplier price list AED 2025"`, `"Dubai building materials wholesale price"`
   - Trends: `"UAE interior design trends 2026"`, `"Dubai luxury residential design report"`
   - Developers: `"Dubai new luxury project launch 2026 interior specifications"`
2. Call Firecrawl search API for each query (limit: 10 results)
3. Filter out already-registered URLs (check `source_registry.url`)
4. For new URLs: test-scrape (1 page, extract up to 5 items)
5. Use Gemini to evaluate: "Is this a reliable UAE market data source? Grade A/B/C?"
6. Return candidates for admin review OR auto-register Grade A/B sources

#### [MODIFY] [ingestion.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/routers/ingestion.ts)

Add endpoints:
- `discoverSources` — Run source discovery (admin-only, returns candidates)
- `approveDiscoveredSource` — Register a discovered source

#### [MODIFY] [scheduler.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/scheduler.ts)

Add optional monthly source discovery cron (1st of each month).

---

### Module H: DB Value Cross-Verification

**Problem:** Existing `evidence_records` values may have drifted from reality.  
**Solution:** Periodic verification that compares DB values against fresh scrapes.

#### [NEW] [data-verifier.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/data-verifier.ts)

```typescript
interface VerificationResult {
  recordId: string;
  itemName: string;
  dbValue: number;
  freshValue: number | null;
  deltaPct: number;
  status: "confirmed" | "drifted" | "source_unavailable";
}

async function verifyExistingRecords(
  category?: string,
  limit?: number
): Promise<VerificationResult[]>
```

**Flow:**
1. Take a random sample of evidence_records (50 per run)
2. Re-fetch the `sourceUrl` for each record
3. Re-run LLM extraction on fresh content
4. Compare: if delta > 15%, flag as "drifted" + trigger upsert
5. If source returns 404/403, flag as "source_unavailable"
6. Log all results to `intelligence_audit_log`

#### [MODIFY] [ingestion.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/routers/ingestion.ts)

Add `verifyData` endpoint for manual trigger.

#### [MODIFY] [scheduler.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/scheduler.ts)

Add bi-weekly verification cron (1st and 15th).

